The Ambassador of Nigeria to the Russian Federation, Prof. Abdullahi Y. Shehu has stressed the need for more collaborative efforts towards a heightened Foreign Direct Investments (FDI) from Russia to Nigeria. A statement from the Nigerian embassy in Moscow said the envoy made the call during a courtesy call on him by the Nigerians in Diaspora, Russia (NIDO-RUSSIA), led by the groupâ€™s chairman, Uwem-Edimo Sampson. Mr. Sampson noted that, the main mandate of NIDO-RUSSIA is the actualization of a stronger trade and economic ties between Nigeria and Russia. Ambassador Shehu, while noting the efforts of NIDO-RUSSIA in various investment activities between Nigeria and Russia, said stronger collaboration is needed towards actualizing the main Foreign Policy thrust of Nigeria which is Citizen Diplomacy.